00:31:44.000 --> 00:31:47.620
So this expression
is, in general, fine.

00:31:47.620 --> 00:31:49.780
But whenever you have
perturbation theory,

00:31:49.780 --> 00:31:51.670
you start to evaluate
things and you

00:31:51.670 --> 00:31:54.430
have to see whether
the correction indeed

00:31:54.430 --> 00:31:56.100
is sufficiently small.

00:31:56.100 --> 00:31:58.500
And it seems we can't make
it sufficiently small.

00:31:58.500 --> 00:31:59.384
Yes.

