Part of it is this bl
to the power of nl,

01:13:04.980 --> 01:13:08.790
and then I have the contribution
that is nl factorial l

01:13:08.790 --> 01:13:10.236
factorial to the power of nl.

01:13:15.930 --> 01:13:17.150
So this part cancels.

01:13:19.840 --> 01:13:25.360
For each l, I can
now independently

01:13:25.360 --> 01:13:31.910
sum over the values of nl can
be anything, 0 to infinity.

01:13:31.910 --> 01:13:33.762
And what do I have?

01:13:33.762 --> 01:13:39.650
I have bl to the power of nl.

01:13:39.650 --> 01:13:43.790
I have division by nl factorial.

01:13:43.790 --> 01:13:48.630
I have l factorial
to the power of nl.

01:13:48.630 --> 01:13:55.920
And then I have e to the beta
mu over lambda cubed raised

01:13:55.920 --> 01:13:57.431
to the power of l nl.

01:14:08.500 --> 01:14:12.650
I recognize that each one
of these terms in the sum

01:14:12.650 --> 01:14:19.150
is 1 over nl factorial something
raised to the power of nl,

01:14:19.150 --> 01:14:22.240
which is the definition
of the exponential.

01:14:22.240 --> 01:14:27.880
So my q is a product
over all l's.

01:14:27.880 --> 01:14:35.690
Once I exponentiate, I
have e to the beta mu

01:14:35.690 --> 01:14:42.380
over lambda cubed raised
to the power of l.

01:14:42.380 --> 01:14:46.890
And then I have bl
divided by l factorial.

01:14:53.080 --> 01:14:59.770
Or, log of Q, which is the
quantity that I'm interested,

01:14:59.770 --> 01:15:04.240
is obtained by summing
over all clusters 1

01:15:04.240 --> 01:15:11.290
to infinity e to the beta
mu over lambda cubed raised

01:15:11.290 --> 01:15:16.366
to the power of l bl
divided by l factorial.

01:15:26.840 --> 01:15:30.330
So what does this
tell us, which is

01:15:30.330 --> 01:15:34.050
kind of nice and
fundamentally important?

01:15:34.050 --> 01:15:38.110
You see, we started at
the beginning over here

01:15:38.110 --> 01:15:40.510
with a huge number of graphs.

01:15:43.280 --> 01:15:49.240
These graphs could be organizing
all kinds of clusters.

01:15:49.240 --> 01:15:51.980
And they would give us
either the partition function

01:15:51.980 --> 01:15:56.700
or summing over N, the
grand partition function.

01:15:56.700 --> 01:16:05.230
But when we take the log, I get
only single connect objects.

01:16:05.230 --> 01:16:07.510
And this is something
that you had already

01:16:07.510 --> 01:16:10.440
seen as the connection
that we have

01:16:10.440 --> 01:16:13.750
between moments and Cumulants.

01:16:13.750 --> 01:16:17.010
So the way that we
got Cumulants was

01:16:17.010 --> 01:16:19.860
to look at the
expansion of the log.

01:16:19.860 --> 01:16:23.250
So the function itself was
the generator of all moments

01:16:23.250 --> 01:16:24.830
and we took the log.

01:16:24.830 --> 01:16:26.990
And graphically,
we presented that

01:16:26.990 --> 01:16:29.480
as getting the moments
by putting together

01:16:29.480 --> 01:16:34.920
all kinds of clusters of points
that corresponded to Cumulants.

01:16:34.920 --> 01:16:37.300
And this is again,
a representation

01:16:37.300 --> 01:16:38.660
of the same thing.

01:16:38.660 --> 01:16:41.490
That is, in the log
you have essentially

01:16:41.490 --> 01:16:44.290
individual contributions.

01:16:44.290 --> 01:16:49.790
Once you exponentiated, you
get multiple contributions.

01:16:49.790 --> 01:16:54.870
Now, the other thing is, that
if I am thinking about the gas,

01:16:54.870 --> 01:17:00.730
then log of Q is e
to the minus beta g.

01:17:00.730 --> 01:17:11.270
And g is E minus TS minus
mu N. Bur for a gas that

01:17:11.270 --> 01:17:16.840
has extensive properties,
E is TS mu N minus PV.

01:17:16.840 --> 01:17:19.210
So this is the same
thing as beta PV.

01:17:22.320 --> 01:17:25.730
So this quantity that
we have calculated here

01:17:25.730 --> 01:17:27.830
is, in fact, related
to the pressure

01:17:27.830 --> 01:17:30.001
directly through this formula.

01:17:32.810 --> 01:17:35.770
And the important part or
the important observation

01:17:35.770 --> 01:17:40.800
is that it says that it should
be proportional to volume.

01:17:40.800 --> 01:17:44.170
You can see that
each one of my b's

01:17:44.170 --> 01:17:48.500
that I calculated here will
have one free integral.

01:17:48.500 --> 01:17:50.010
If you like, its center of mass.

01:17:50.010 --> 01:17:52.310
You can go over
the entire volume.

01:17:52.310 --> 01:17:58.560
So all of my b's are indeed
proportionality to volume.

01:17:58.560 --> 01:18:00.440
And you can see what
disaster it would

01:18:00.440 --> 01:18:05.310
have been if there was a term
here that was not just a linked

01:18:05.310 --> 01:18:07.510
cluster but product of
two linked clusters.

01:18:07.510 --> 01:18:10.240
Then I would have something
that would go like V squared.

01:18:10.240 --> 01:18:12.010
It's not allowed.

01:18:12.010 --> 01:18:16.970
So essentially, this linked
cluster nature is also

01:18:16.970 --> 01:18:19.850
related to extensivity
in this sense.

01:18:23.350 --> 01:18:28.620
So in some sense, what I have
established here-- again,

01:18:28.620 --> 01:18:35.170
related to that-- is that
clearly all of my bl's

01:18:35.170 --> 01:18:38.650
are proportional to volume.

01:18:38.650 --> 01:18:40.510
And I can define
something that I

01:18:40.510 --> 01:18:48.540
will call bl bar, which is
divide the thing by the volume.

01:18:48.540 --> 01:18:54.770
And then what we
have established

01:18:54.770 --> 01:19:03.400
is that the pressure of this
interacting gas as an expansion

01:19:03.400 --> 01:19:09.142
beta p, which takes this
nice, simple form, sum over l

01:19:09.142 --> 01:19:14.770
e to the beta mu divided
by lambda cubed bl

01:19:14.770 --> 01:19:21.580
bar-- the intensive part of the
contribution of these cluster--

01:19:21.580 --> 01:19:23.300
divided by l factorial.

01:19:23.300 --> 01:19:26.540
This, of course, runs
from 1 to [INAUDIBLE].

01:19:29.510 --> 01:19:30.070
Yes.

01:19:30.070 --> 01:19:33.592
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]
is raised to the l?

01:19:33.592 --> 01:19:35.133
PROFESSOR: Who's
asking the question?

01:19:35.133 --> 01:19:37.999
AUDIENCE: The term in the
parentheses is raised to the l?

01:19:37.999 --> 01:19:38.790
PROFESSOR: Exactly.

01:19:38.790 --> 01:19:42.120
Thank you very much.

01:19:42.120 --> 01:19:43.534
Yes.

01:19:43.534 --> 01:19:44.450
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE].

01:19:53.575 --> 01:19:55.930
But they don't, actually.

01:19:55.930 --> 01:19:58.870
Could that be true, for
example [INAUDIBLE]?

01:20:04.667 --> 01:20:05.250
PROFESSOR: OK.

01:20:05.250 --> 01:20:07.750
So the triangle, I have it here.

01:20:07.750 --> 01:20:12.320
Integral d q1, d q2, d
Q3, f 1 2, f 2 3, f 3.

01:20:12.320 --> 01:20:14.370
Let's write it explicitly.

01:20:14.370 --> 01:20:23.210
It is f of q1 minus q2, f of
q2 minus q3, f of q3 minus q1.

01:20:23.210 --> 01:20:25.725
I call this vector x.

01:20:25.725 --> 01:20:28.500
I call that vector y.

01:20:28.500 --> 01:20:30.700
This vector is x plus y.

01:20:35.310 --> 01:20:36.109
Yes.

01:20:36.109 --> 01:20:38.504
AUDIENCE: Does the
contribution from [INAUDIBLE]?

01:20:44.260 --> 01:20:45.290
PROFESSOR: OK.

01:20:45.290 --> 01:20:52.720
So you say that I have here
an expansion for the pressure.

01:20:52.720 --> 01:20:55.930
I had given you previously
an expansion for pressure

01:20:55.930 --> 01:20:59.240
that I said is sensible, which
is this Virial expansion, which

01:20:59.240 --> 01:21:01.870
is powers of density.

01:21:01.870 --> 01:21:06.160
This is not an expansion
in powers of density.

01:21:06.160 --> 01:21:10.320
So whether or not the
terms in this expansion

01:21:10.320 --> 01:21:13.230
becomes smaller or
larger will depend

01:21:13.230 --> 01:21:16.490
on density in some indirect way.

01:21:16.490 --> 01:21:21.100
So my next task, which
I will do next lecture,

01:21:21.100 --> 01:21:23.540
is within this ensemble
I have told you

01:21:23.540 --> 01:21:25.740
what the chemical potential is.

01:21:25.740 --> 01:21:28.160
Once I know what the
chemical potential is,

01:21:28.160 --> 01:21:30.770
I can calculate the
number of particles

01:21:30.770 --> 01:21:36.380
as d log Q by d beta mu.

01:21:36.380 --> 01:21:41.640
And hence, I can calculate
what the density is.

01:21:41.640 --> 01:21:46.390
And so the answer for this will
also be a series in powers of e

01:21:46.390 --> 01:21:47.980
to the beta mu.

01:21:47.980 --> 01:21:51.280
And what then I will do is
I will combine these two

01:21:51.280 --> 01:21:56.620
series to get an expansion for
pressure in powers of density,

01:21:56.620 --> 01:22:00.410
and then identify the
convergence of this series

01:22:00.410 --> 01:22:03.320
and all of that
via that procedure.

